			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AE nerf inc for tomorrow?<a name="60224"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 3 04 11:31 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>We're not saying bards should be stationary. Being able to move about and cast spells is part of what bards have always been able to do and while I can't speak for the design team I really don't expect that to change. The problem with the PBAE is that people were using these spells to gain experience at a rate far beyond what the designers felt was reasonable. Quite a lot of time was spent discussing this, and dropping the range of damage causing PBAE spells to melee range of the NPC when the bard is running around seemed to be the only practical way to solve this fairly substantial balance problem. Not only is it a balance problem, but it's also a general server load problem since this PBAE kiting puts a fairly large strain on the server clusters and does in fact cause server lag for other players.
<br />

<br />
That said, if you feel there is a better way to stop people from being able to AE kite dozens/hundreds of NPCs at a single time that would have less side effects to gameplay than the change currently in place, please let us know. We just want to solve the problem. Personally I think this is a reasonable solution but I will be happy to pass ideas off to the design team. Like all code on Test, it's subject to change so now is a good time to come up with better ideas.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
