				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AE nerf inc for tomorrow?<a name="60282"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 3 04 3:33 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I am a 65 bard. I've played solo and small group for most of my career. I have never AE kited in that time. Any bard who claims to have lost the ability to solo because of this fix is quite simply mistaken. There are still plenty of other ways to solo a bard.
<br />

<br />
I happened upon a bard who was soloing Dulak this past weekend with AE kiting. He was a level 52 bard, and he had pulled a large fraction of the zone into the wide open area just as you enter the zone. Inside 10 minutes or so, he'd killed all of them, and he was now a 54 bard. Gained over a level in a single kite. Yes, absolutely, that is horribly unbalanced.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I don't think your fix is going to work. You said the range was unchanged while the bard stands still, but limited to melee range while moving. Fine. The new tactic is to pull the whole zone, run far enough ahead of the bunch, stop, cast, and get moving again as soon as the song goes off, before they catch you. You were not moving during the cast, and the mobs quite happily moved into the full stationary range without quite getting close enough to hit you. Yes, it's more risky, but you'll still have bards in Dulak gaining levels at a time, just running around more of the zone to do it.
<br />

<br />
The one place that I do use my AoE songs is for green farming. I'm perfectly willing to let 40-odd green mobs beat on me for the 4 or 5 ticks it takes them to die. So in that case your fix would not affect me. Limiting the number of mobs I can hit to 10 would affect me. It would be annoying, but hardly intolerable.
<br />

<br />
Why not just put a hard cap on the EXP gain rate? Seems to solve the problem without changing the rest of the song dynamics. Also solves the problem of 65's powerlevelling low characters. (Assuming you see that as a problem.) Then again, I suppose a patient bard could just run around with a huge kite in tow waiting for more time before killing again, but why? It's far more risky then running a few small kites in the same time. </span></td>
