				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AE nerf inc for tomorrow?<a name="60288"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 3 04 3:53 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>No you cannot still pull 50 mobs and continue to kite. In HoH the mobs gate over 10. That is the fix. It does not create trains, as if the mob runs back chances are he will smack you, not just get right back in line. Welcome to squished bard.
<br />

<br />
 As I mentioned on another board, This is imo the most reasonable fix, the 10 mob rule. This could be balanced and lessened even further. Nerf the range on the songs, and let EN work it back up to its current range.
<br />

<br />
This does two things-
<br />
It negates the use of AE as viable until 51. Ergo, no level a kite at level 5, or 30, no low level zone monopolizing. No one will save the aa necessary to make this viable again until they get the levels first. Perhaps very very few will spend on it once they hit 51, but it won't be worth it, if the 10 mob rule is in effect.
<br />

<br />
It drastically reduces the amount of zones AE will have to be adjusted to the 10 mob rule, making SoE lives easier. Here are the zones as I know them. Please folks, if you know others, mention them- it is for our benefit.
<br />
Dulak, Gunthak, Nadox, PoV, PoN, ME. If it is the lower level bard that is the problem , no zones need adjusting at all.
<br />

<br />
2aa an hour is not overpowering nor unbalanced. Work a solution around that premise. If SoE thinks it is, state so.
<br />

<br />
Standing and casting is unfortunately, not a workable solution for these reasons- First of all, Bards are always moving, it is second nature. Second of all, in groups and raids there is a matter of position. It is not a targeted AE, where we can stand back and cast, we have to get in the middle, that means moving, and due to the lag generated by a raid, you are asking for an exact instant in time to be synched, ie stopped when the song hits, or it now becomes ineffective. Our comps must recognize it, the servers must recognize it. If you have to be stopped when the song is started and ends, chances are we will not be in position, that happens at the last second on AE encounters and groups, especially as the bard is often the puller. The current range is not so much that we are guaranteed a hit unless we are in the middle.
<br />

<br />
Extend the AE range to pre-nerf HoH levels to solve the above mentioend issue, and you will still have AE kiters btw, the only difference is that the motion will be stutter step, the circles will be bigger is all. It will get rid of autocircling however, but it would not solve the root issue. It will just mean a new technique to learn.
<br />

<br />
I am however glad to see that indeed the squeaky wheel does get the grease, fix it right. If any of my posts seemed incendiary to you, good, they were intended to be. We have someone talking to us now, at the very least.
