<br />

<br />
Thanks for taking the time to explain what is going to happen.  I hope you're 100% right on how you say this change is going to be.
<br />

<br />
To everyone else, yeah, there are other fixes that could have been put into place, such as the fix for HoH or turning our AE Kiting into Quad Kiting... but even that comparison is wrong.  We use no mana, can run the whole time, and AE Kite... that's not quadding at all.  So, maybe there were a couple other possible fixes, but I fail to see how this fix (if done as stated) will affect anything other than the AE Kiters.
<br />

<br />
I have AE Kited some myself, to see what all the buzz was about; honestly, I think it probably did need a bit of a nerf.  I'm not saying it's horribly over-powered in my case, since I'm not that great at researching and timing things, but someone who was, could get tons of returns with very little risk... I can see that being a problem.  Due to areas being cleared constantly, some of the inconsiderate Bards out there who will take all mobs from in front of people, and thanks to the many Bards who got tons of levels and had no clue how to play their class, I think this is a change for the better.  I will be sad to see the 30-40% lvl exp per kite at ~lvl 40 go, but it really was ridiculous... I had been justifying it with the number of deaths I take, but I still out leveled my Wizard, SK and Monk friends almost 2 levels to 1.  
<br />

<br />
I do hope that maybe the developers start looking at ways to give a bit of a boost to Bards since it seems to be the consensus that you need hundreds of AA in order to be decent, and that was only bearable before because of the nice exp we could solo.  There are still other methods of soloing and getting good exp, I'm sure, but probably not much faster than other classes... so we should have the same dependence upon AA's that other classes do.  That is to say, maybe some of our regular abilities need a little tweaking.  
<br />

<br />
Overall, I'm very happy to play a Bard, and this change seems like it is only going to defeat the one thing it aimed to defeat, so nothing wrong with that.  I wonder if they figured for the fact that there would still be a way (even more dangerous) to AE Kite at least at lower levels ( &lt;55 ).  All it would take is even more precise timing of the songs and various 'manuevers'.  If they did take care of that in the code, it may unintentionally step on some of the other ways the songs can be used... we'll see.
<br />

<br />
Personally, if it only affects AE Damage songs (and hopefully only the damage portions of mixed AE damage/effect songs) and only if you're moving, I don't think this is bad at all.
<br />

<br />
I hope the friendly, helpful, mature Bards among you who play Bards because you want to be Bards stay with the class... those who wanted fast levels or whatever else... make your way over to the quadder classes now.  And on that note, Druids and Wizzies, now that people are going to stop bitching about us (I would hope) I wish you the best of luck at being a target once again now that you can effectively kill the most mobs simultaneously of the classes.
<br />

<br />
-ST</span></td>
